        <div><a name="_f2ba2169-4856-d68c-28a6-c6105f4c88e3" id="_f2ba2169-4856-d68c-28a6-c6105f4c88e3"></a><h2>7.5.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Mechanism Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_1c1a8f8c-204b-bcb6-6312-ab02eff049f7" id="_1c1a8f8c-204b-bcb6-6312-ab02eff049f7"></a>A Mechanism is a classification of the specific physical, chemical, or operational process that constitutes the direct cause or pathway for an emission. It is defined independently of the Source&#x2014;including its identity, structure, or purpose&#x2014;allowing Mechanisms to be consistently reused across different types of Source.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 16</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_e0610786-1186-6b1c-84b3-c8d2a130e004" id="_e0610786-1186-6b1c-84b3-c8d2a130e004"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 4: Mechanism Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/mechanism<br/> + Each Mechanism class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#mechanism-attributes">Table 17</a>. Each Mechanism class shall have the direct relation listed in  <a href="#mechanism-relations">Table 18</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 17&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of a Mechanism class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="mechanism-attributes" id="mechanism-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">label</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">A human-readable label for the mechanism.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">CharacterString</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">description</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">A detailed description of the mechanism.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">CharacterString</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">0..1 (optional)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 18&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between a Mechanism class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="mechanism-relations" id="mechanism-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">hasIntent</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The emission intent associated with the mechanism.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">EmissionIntent</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_e9c94327-5891-2bbf-78dd-9ed888e5f05c" id="_e9c94327-5891-2bbf-78dd-9ed888e5f05c"></a><h2>7.6.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Emission Quantity Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_01772ddf-8e4a-6d97-f889-57fece2b02c3" id="_01772ddf-8e4a-6d97-f889-57fece2b02c3"></a>An Emission Quantity is the physical quantity representing the total mass of substance released to the atmosphere during a defined Emission Event or over a specified time interval.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 19</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_209b2960-b8b3-ea61-b249-4a46b38cd5d2" id="_209b2960-b8b3-ea61-b249-4a46b38cd5d2"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 5: Emission Quantity Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/emission-quantity<br/> + Each Emission Quantity class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#emission-quantity-attributes">Table 20</a>. Each Emission Quantity class shall have the direct relation between an Emission Quantity class and other classes listed in  <a href="#emission-quantity-relations">Table 21</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 20&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of an Emission Quantity class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="emission-quantity-attributes" id="emission-quantity-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">value</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The numeric value of the emission quantity.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Real</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">quality</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">A data quality element describing the quality of the emission quantity value.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">DQ_Element</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">0..* (optional)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 21&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between an Emission Quantity class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="emission-quantity-relations" id="emission-quantity-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">hasUnit</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The unit of measure associated with the emission quantity.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">UnitOfMeasure</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_fb9175cb-6649-2c54-7be5-076ddc8eae30" id="_fb9175cb-6649-2c54-7be5-076ddc8eae30"></a><h2>7.7.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Unit of Measure Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_9259e655-8c9e-8685-00ff-77daa0318d44" id="_9259e655-8c9e-8685-00ff-77daa0318d44"></a>A Unit of Measure is a reference quantity chosen from a unit equivalence group (Source: ISO/OGC 19156:2023)</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 22</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_2a7a68fd-8f12-650f-eb95-150d17125489" id="_2a7a68fd-8f12-650f-eb95-150d17125489"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 6: Unit of Measure Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/unit-of-measure<br/> + Each Unit of Measure class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#unit-of-measure-attributes">Table 23</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 23&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of a Unit of Measure class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="unit-of-measure-attributes" id="unit-of-measure-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">label</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">A human-readable label for the unit of measure.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">CharacterString</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">symbol</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">A short symbol representing the unit of measure.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">CharacterString</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">definition</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The URI linking to an external definition of the unit of measure.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">URI</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 24&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between a Unit of Measure class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="unit-of-measure-relations" id="unit-of-measure-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">No direct relations are defined for UnitOfMeasure in the core model.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_e392bc7d-89ca-4696-e2ae-4b791e21203e" id="_e392bc7d-89ca-4696-e2ae-4b791e21203e"></a><h2>7.8.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Temporal Bound Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_ce101dc3-b2c2-acc9-eab5-6049e371f1b6" id="_ce101dc3-b2c2-acc9-eab5-6049e371f1b6"></a>A Temporal Bound is a value object representing a temporal determination (e.g., start time or end time) that MAY have associated data quality metadata. The determination procedure and supporting evidence for a Temporal Bound are tracked at the Emission Event level.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 25</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_d0627b59-bb7e-f847-40ab-924f007aba4a" id="_d0627b59-bb7e-f847-40ab-924f007aba4a"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 7: Temporal Bound Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/temporal-bound<br/> + Each Temporal Bound class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#temporal-bound-attributes">Table 26</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 26&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of a Temporal Bound class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="temporal-bound-attributes" id="temporal-bound-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">time</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The time instant value of this Temporal Bound.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">TM_Instant</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">quality</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">A data quality element describing the quality of the temporal bound.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">DQ_Element</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">0..* (optional)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 27&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between a Temporal Bound class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="temporal-bound-relations" id="temporal-bound-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">No direct relations are defined for TemporalBound in the core model (determination procedure and evidence are tracked at the EmissionEvent level).</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_fe6f52fc-26b1-8727-4c64-3008f85febb8" id="_fe6f52fc-26b1-8727-4c64-3008f85febb8"></a><h2>7.9.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Observation Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_d87d7594-9dc4-aa05-3685-cd0de5bb04b5" id="_d87d7594-9dc4-aa05-3685-cd0de5bb04b5"></a>An Observation is an act carried out by an observer to determine the value of an observable property of an object (feature-of-interest) by using a procedure, with the value provided as the result (Source: ISO/OGC 19156:2023). In EmissionML, an Observation is evidence that may support an Emission Quantity or Temporal Bound determination.</p><div class="Note"><a name="_d63db42e-d085-fdf1-8d47-debea4c2baf9" id="_d63db42e-d085-fdf1-8d47-debea4c2baf9"></a><p class="Note"><span class="note_label">NOTE:<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span></span>The Ultimate Feature of Interest of an Observation identifies a Feature &#x2014; which may be a Source or another feature at a different spatial scale &#x2014; associated with the Emission Event. It is common for a single Emission Event to be observed by multiple Observations whose Ultimate Features of Interest are defined at different spatial scales. For example, a satellite remote sensing image Observation typically has an area-based Ultimate Feature of Interest (e.g., a facility area or region), whereas the same Emission Event may also be observed by a person carrying an Optical Gas Imaging camera, for which the Ultimate Feature of Interest is a specific Source such as a component of an item of equipment from which pollutants are released.</p></div>



<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 28</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_91beda61-65ab-2e72-699d-658e502ee09a" id="_91beda61-65ab-2e72-699d-658e502ee09a"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 8: Observation Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/observation<br/> + Each Observation class shall be an ISO/OGC 19156:2023 (OGC OMS 3.0) Observation.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_7dd30f58-2b5a-245d-e8e0-eb3476caa9f9" id="_7dd30f58-2b5a-245d-e8e0-eb3476caa9f9"></a><h2>7.10.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Emission Intent Enumeration</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_7fc19d0d-aacd-a29d-7490-cf290736e9b4" id="_7fc19d0d-aacd-a29d-7490-cf290736e9b4"></a>Emission Intent is a code list describing whether an emission is intentional, unintentional, or unknown.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 29</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_81fd51f5-ada4-d80c-3dc8-c6412598b425" id="_81fd51f5-ada4-d80c-3dc8-c6412598b425"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 9: Emission Intent Enumeration </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/emission-intent<br/> + The Emission Intent enumeration shall support the enumeration values listed in  <a href="#emission-intent-values">Table 30</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 30&#xA0;&#x2014; Enumeration values of Emission Intent</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="emission-intent-values" id="emission-intent-values"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Name</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">intentional</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The emission occurred intentionally.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">unintentional</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The emission occurred unintentionally.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">unknown</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The intent of the emission is unknown.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_7d2bdbd5-00fd-5350-4515-58b811a7e0b6" id="_7d2bdbd5-00fd-5350-4515-58b811a7e0b6"></a><h2>7.11.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Procedure Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_9dddc4cc-c03e-babb-6162-79024fe59008" id="_9dddc4cc-c03e-babb-6162-79024fe59008"></a>A Procedure is a description of steps performed (Source: ISO/OGC 19156:2023). In EmissionML, Procedure serves as the base class for process descriptions such as DeterminationProcedure.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 31</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_e9ae971c-a33a-221b-10cc-5247318ab621" id="_e9ae971c-a33a-221b-10cc-5247318ab621"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 12: Procedure Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/procedure<br/> + Each Procedure class shall be an ISO/OGC 19156:2023 (OGC OMS 3.0) Procedure.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 32&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of a Procedure class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="procedure-attributes" id="procedure-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">No own attributes are defined for Procedure in the core model (see the standard for complete specification).</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 33&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between a Procedure class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="procedure-relations" id="procedure-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">No direct relations are defined for Procedure in the core model (it is referenced by DeterminationProcedure via inheritance).</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_07c6b043-b2c6-1e70-f4c4-15861d0a4692" id="_07c6b043-b2c6-1e70-f4c4-15861d0a4692"></a><h2>7.12.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Determination Procedure Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_5b4a9639-4003-dd47-1f08-434153d748c9" id="_5b4a9639-4003-dd47-1f08-434153d748c9"></a>A Determination Procedure describes the steps performed to determine the quantity or temporal bounds of an Emission Event. DeterminationProcedure inherits from Procedure, aligning it with the OMS 3.0 process model.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 34</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_9f7515da-53b2-a699-f365-e02c030c878c" id="_9f7515da-53b2-a699-f365-e02c030c878c"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 10: Determination Procedure Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/determination-procedure<br/> + Each Determination Procedure class shall inherit from Procedure. Each Determination Procedure class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#determination-procedure-attributes">Table 35</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 35&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of a Determination Procedure class (own attributes)</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="determination-procedure-attributes" id="determination-procedure-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">label</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">A human-readable label for the determination procedure.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">CharacterString</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">description</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">A detailed description of the determination procedure.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">CharacterString</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">0..1 (optional)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">definition</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The URI linking to an external definition of the determination procedure.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">URI</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">0..1 (optional)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
</div>
